      "date": "2019-04-17 15:38:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n(7 comments)\n\nI think the changes could be reduced further, to keep the functionality needed by Elena's patch, while reverting only the changes to the stripe count and MDT index that seem to be causing the test failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "0f2a6f8fc8d90bd74be77b26e263a54f5fe0e4fe",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-04-17 16:11:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nSince we're not sure which parts are causing the problem - the affected tests do not deliberately interact with any specific MDS, so there's no obvious connection to this change - I'd like to start with this bigger revert and run it through testing.  I can also spin up a reduced version per your suggestions and push it separately to test that as well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "7df2c6a73fdb8e941361cee4d435b875828f43e6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 464,
        "name": "Elena",
        "email": "elena.gryaznova@hpe.com",
        "username": "elena"
      },
      "date": "2019-04-17 16:18:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\ncommit message does not explain the reasons why this patch is required.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "e7510580ccc68fa79d3ce788866b11ae97ce70d2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-04-17 16:20:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nYes, of course - Sorry, this is just to get testing started.  I did not mark as \"fortestonly\" because I don't want it to do a reduced test set - I want it to run everything as well as the extra tests in test-parameters.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "96a3324b984d4101d6473a0268288699c66b1e1d",
      "author": {
